{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-template-excerpt-js","path":"/excerpts/nature_bare_trees/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Fracture lines cut in a bleak sky,<br>\nStripped bare across the countryside,<br>\nShadows of what they used to be,<br>\nSilhouetted so beautifully,<br>\nNo more a haven to make a home,<br>\nFragile looking veins are exposed,<br>\nSun bleeds through while blindingly low,<br>\nWood spirits are compelled to go,<br>\nA sight rooted in these cold months,<br>\nCrafted by a cruel lack of warmth,<br>\nWeather the sky gods issue forth,<br>\nSent to the front line from the north,<br>\nBut trees fear not old man winter,<br>\nHis firm grip can't last forever,<br>\nSoon things will be back as they were,<br>\nTill the changes again occur.</p>","frontmatter":{"date":"January 14, 2020","title":"Bare Trees","audio":{"publicURL":"/static/861637cfd6ca077963161a538331fe14/Christian Lacdael - Nature - 14 Bare Trees.mp3"},"icon":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/069ff5bf11cd51cacaf5ccf2480e9119/3c17d/nature_poem_bare_trees.png","srcSet":"/static/069ff5bf11cd51cacaf5ccf2480e9119/69585/nature_poem_bare_trees.png 200w,\n/static/069ff5bf11cd51cacaf5ccf2480e9119/497c6/nature_poem_bare_trees.png 400w,\n/static/069ff5bf11cd51cacaf5ccf2480e9119/3c17d/nature_poem_bare_trees.png 720w","sizes":"(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/excerpts/nature_bare_trees/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["3649515864"]}